      <hedline>
        <hl1>Party of 18</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Lynn Andriani letter on Seth Margolis's April 9 travel article says family of 18 has been vacationing at Puerto Rico's Palmas del Mar resort since 19850</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor: Seth Margolis's article on the Puerto Rican resort Palmas del Mar, ''Balancing Act for a Party of 18'' (April 9), hits the nail right on the head. Mr. Margolis has recently discovered a treasure that my family has known for over 15 years. Our family of 18 has been vacationing at Palmas since 1985. Every February, we've made the trek from New Jersey to spend a week together at the beach.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor: Seth Margolis's article on the Puerto Rican resort Palmas del Mar, ''Balancing Act for a Party of 18'' (April 9), hits the nail right on the head. Mr. Margolis has recently discovered a treasure that my family has known for over 15 years. Our family of 18 has been vacationing at Palmas since 1985. Every February, we've made the trek from New Jersey to spend a week together at the beach.</p>
        <p>Over the years we've seen Palmas grow and change, for better or worse. But it is a sort of second home to us all -- and finding Mr. Margolis's piece was a surprise and a delight.</p>
        <p>LYNN ANDRIANI  New York, N.Y.</p>
      </block>
